# Custom Theme System for T3 Code

## Context

The app has a minimal light/dark/system toggle (`apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`) that only flips a `dark` class on `<html>`. The request is to build a full custom theme system with named visual themes that each own a complete color palette (background, foreground, accent, sidebar, editor, terminal, status bar), persist to localStorage, apply as CSS custom properties, and expose a selector UI with preview swatches. The type contract lives in `packages/shared` (plain TS, no Effect); the provider, hook, and selector live in `apps/web`. No build config changes or new dependencies.

---

## Files to Modify / Create

| Action | Path |
|--------|------|
| CREATE | `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` |
| MODIFY | `packages/shared/package.json` |
| REWRITE | `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` |
| CREATE | `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx` |
| CREATE | `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` |
| MODIFY | `apps/web/src/routes/__root.tsx` |
| MODIFY | `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` |
| MODIFY | `apps/web/src/index.css` |

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — Define theme types in `packages/shared/src/theme.ts`

Pure TypeScript — no Effect Schema. This module is consumed by both the web app and potentially the server in the future.

```typescript
export type ThemeId = "t3-dark" | "t3-light" | "t3-midnight";

export type ThemeColorSlots = {
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  accent: string;
  sidebar: string;
  editor: string;
  terminal: string;
  statusBar: string;
};

export type ThemeDefinition = {
  readonly id: ThemeId;
  readonly name: string;
  readonly isDark: boolean;
  readonly colors: ThemeColorSlots;
};

export const BUILT_IN_THEMES = [
  {
    id: "t3-light",
    name: "T3 Light",
    isDark: false,
    colors: {
      background: "#ffffff",
      foreground: "#1a1a1a",
      accent: "oklch(0.488 0.217 264)",
      sidebar: "#f0f0f0",
      editor: "#fafafa",
      terminal: "#f5f5f5",
      statusBar: "#e8e8e8",
    },
  },
  {
    id: "t3-dark",
    name: "T3 Dark",
    isDark: true,
    colors: {
      background: "#0e0e10",
      foreground: "#e2e2e6",
      accent: "oklch(0.588 0.217 264)",
      sidebar: "#09090b",
      editor: "#0e0e10",
      terminal: "#09090b",
      statusBar: "#060608",
    },
  },
  {
    id: "t3-midnight",
    name: "T3 Midnight",
    isDark: true,
    colors: {
      background: "#0d1117",
      foreground: "#c9d1d9",
      accent: "#58a6ff",
      sidebar: "#0a0d13",
      editor: "#0d1117",
      terminal: "#0a0d13",
      statusBar: "#161b22",
    },
  },
] as const satisfies readonly ThemeDefinition[];

export const DEFAULT_THEME_ID: ThemeId = "t3-dark";

// Keyed lookup for O(1) access by id
export const BUILT_IN_THEMES_BY_ID = Object.fromEntries(
  BUILT_IN_THEMES.map((t) => [t.id, t]),
) as Record<ThemeId, ThemeDefinition>;
```

### Step 2 — Add subpath export to `packages/shared/package.json`

Add `"./theme"` alongside the existing `"./model"`, `"./git"`, etc. exports:

```json
"./theme": {
  "types": "./src/theme.ts",
  "import": "./src/theme.ts"
}
```

### Step 3 — Rewrite `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`

Replace the existing light/dark/system hook entirely. Preserve the same module-level external-store pattern (`useSyncExternalStore` + listeners array) that the file already uses — this prevents FOUC by running `applyTheme()` at module load before React renders.

Key behavior:
- Storage key: `"t3code:theme"` (reuse existing key; unknown/legacy values fall back to `DEFAULT_THEME_ID`)
- `applyTheme(themeId)`: toggles `.dark` class on `document.documentElement` (keeps shadcn dark-mode variants working) AND sets CSS custom properties directly via `document.documentElement.style.setProperty(...)` for each color slot
- CSS properties set: `--background`, `--foreground`, `--accent` (override shadcn defaults), plus new props `--t3-sidebar`, `--t3-editor`, `--t3-terminal`, `--t3-status-bar`
- Setting inline style properties on `documentElement` has highest precedence — safely overrides the `:root {}` and `.dark {}` blocks in `index.css`
- `useTheme()` returns `{ themeId, theme, setTheme }` where `theme` is the full `ThemeDefinition` object
- Keep cross-tab sync via `storage` event

```typescript
// module-level state (mirrors existing pattern in this file)
let listeners: Array<() => void> = [];
let lastSnapshot: ThemeSnapshot | null = null;

const STORAGE_KEY = "t3code:theme";

function getStoredThemeId(): ThemeId { ... }
function applyTheme(themeId: ThemeId, suppressTransitions = false) {
  // 1. Toggle .dark class
  // 2. Apply inline CSS custom properties for all color slots
}
// Apply at module load — prevents FOUC
applyTheme(getStoredThemeId());

export function useTheme() {
  const snapshot = useSyncExternalStore(subscribe, getSnapshot);
  const setTheme = useCallback((id: ThemeId) => { ... }, []);
  return { themeId: snapshot.themeId, theme: snapshot.theme, setTheme } as const;
}
```

### Step 4 — Create `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx`

A thin React context provider. Internally calls `useTheme()` (which uses the external store) and re-exposes it via `ThemeContext`. This lets deeply nested components consume typed theme data without prop drilling, and provides the canonical "provider" API requested.

```typescript
export const ThemeContext = React.createContext<ReturnType<typeof useTheme> | null>(null);

export function ThemeProvider({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const value = useTheme();
  return <ThemeContext value={value}>{children}</ThemeContext>;
}

// Convenience re-export so consumers can import from ThemeProvider
export { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";
```

Note: Because `useTheme` already works via `useSyncExternalStore` (no provider needed), both context consumers and direct hook callers will see the same state. The context is additive.

### Step 5 — Create `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx`

A self-contained component. Uses `useTheme()` directly (no need to import from context).

Layout: a responsive grid (3 columns for 3 themes). Each card shows:
- Theme name (e.g. "T3 Dark")
- A row of 4 color swatches (background, foreground, accent, sidebar) rendered as small `<span>` blocks with inline `background` style from the theme's `colors` object
- A "Selected" badge + highlighted border when active
- `onClick` calls `setTheme(theme.id)`

```typescript
import { BUILT_IN_THEMES } from "@t3tools/shared/theme";
import { useTheme } from "../hooks/useTheme";

export function ThemeSelector() {
  const { themeId, setTheme } = useTheme();
  return (
    <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Theme">
      {BUILT_IN_THEMES.map((theme) => {
        const selected = themeId === theme.id;
        return (
          <button
            key={theme.id}
            type="button"
            role="radio"
            aria-checked={selected}
            onClick={() => setTheme(theme.id)}
            className={`rounded-xl border p-3 text-left transition-colors ${
              selected
                ? "border-primary/60 bg-primary/8"
                : "border-border bg-background hover:bg-accent"
            }`}
          >
            {/* Color swatch strip */}
            <div className="mb-2 flex gap-1">
              {[theme.colors.background, theme.colors.sidebar, theme.colors.accent, theme.colors.foreground].map(
                (color, i) => (
                  <span
                    key={i}
                    className="h-4 w-4 rounded-sm"
                    style={{ background: color }}
                    aria-hidden="true"
                  />
                ),
              )}
            </div>
            <p className="text-xs font-medium text-foreground">{theme.name}</p>
            {selected && (
              <span className="mt-1 inline-block rounded bg-primary/14 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-primary">
                Active
              </span>
            )}
          </button>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Step 6 — Wrap root layout with ThemeProvider in `apps/web/src/routes/__root.tsx`

In `RootRouteView`, import and wrap with `<ThemeProvider>` around (or inside) the existing `ToastProvider` tree:

```tsx
import { ThemeProvider } from "../components/ThemeProvider";

// Inside RootRouteView's JSX:
return (
  <ThemeProvider>
    <ToastProvider>
      <AnchoredToastProvider>
        <EventRouter />
        <DesktopProjectBootstrap />
        <Outlet />
      </AnchoredToastProvider>
    </ToastProvider>
  </ThemeProvider>
);
```

The "connecting" fallback branch doesn't need ThemeProvider since the module-level `applyTheme()` call in `useTheme.ts` already handles FOUC before React mounts.

### Step 7 — Update Appearance section in `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx`

Replace the existing hand-rolled radio group (which used `THEME_OPTIONS` with `"system" | "light" | "dark"` values) with `<ThemeSelector />`. Remove the now-unused `THEME_OPTIONS` const, old `theme`/`setTheme`/`resolvedTheme` destructuring, and inline radio button JSX. Update the section's description text.

```tsx
import { ThemeSelector } from "../components/ThemeSelector";

// In SettingsRouteView — remove: const { theme, setTheme, resolvedTheme } = useTheme();
// Replace the Appearance <section> body with:
<section className="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-card p-5">
  <div className="mb-4">
    <h2 className="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">Appearance</h2>
    <p className="mt-1 text-xs text-muted-foreground">
      Choose a color theme for T3 Code.
    </p>
  </div>
  <ThemeSelector />
</section>
```

### Step 8 — Add CSS fallback variables to `apps/web/src/index.css`

Add fallback/initial values for the new `--t3-*` custom properties inside `:root` so they have defined values before JavaScript runs (server-side rendering safety, although this is a client-only app). These will be immediately overridden by `applyTheme()` at module load.

```css
:root {
  /* existing vars ... */
  --t3-sidebar: var(--background);
  --t3-editor: var(--background);
  --t3-terminal: var(--background);
  --t3-status-bar: var(--background);
}
```

---

## Critical Files Reference

- **Shared module pattern**: `packages/shared/src/model.ts` — plain TS functions, no barrel index
- **Shared package exports**: `packages/shared/package.json` (lines 6–27) — subpath export format to copy
- **Existing theme hook**: `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` — `useSyncExternalStore` pattern, FOUC prevention at module load, listener array, cross-tab sync
- **Settings UI pattern**: `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` — section layout (`rounded-2xl border bg-card p-5`), existing Appearance section (lines 202–243) to replace
- **Root layout**: `apps/web/src/routes/__root.tsx` (lines 36–58) — where ThemeProvider wraps the tree
- **CSS variables**: `apps/web/src/index.css` (lines 64–121) — `:root` and `.dark` blocks; inline style on `documentElement` will override these
- **Component pattern**: any file in `apps/web/src/components/ui/` — `cn()`, Tailwind classes, no default exports

---

